1) What's this ?
----------------

TURBO-JAM is a SHAREWARE game.
We've been working very hard on it for 10 months.
This game only runs on AGA machines (A1200/4000/CD 32 ?)


2) Rules.
---------

The aim of the game is to collect all flags that are in all levels.
Your car is moved by pressing the joystick. If you press it right, your
car will turn right (think you are the driver) remember the ASTEROIDS way
of moving your ship ? It is exactly the same.
This kind of moving may look a bit strange but you'll be used to it very 
quickly.
If you push the joystick up, you'll get extra-speed. Pushing it backwards
will move your car backwards.
The firebutton is used when you've caught a fireball and when you want to 
launch it.

Pressing 'P' will pause the game.
Pressing 'Esc' will abort the current game.


